        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 border-b pb-2">
          ORGI (Office of Registrar General of India)
        </h3>
        <p>
          The Office of Registrar General of India, founded in 1961, is the nodal agency of the Government of India under the Ministry of Home Affairs for arranging, conducting, and analysing demographic surveys such as the Census of India and Linguistic Survey of India.
        </p>
        <p>
          It is responsible for generating data on population statistics including Vital Statistics and implementing the Registration of Births and Deaths Act, 1969, along with reports for Civil Registration System (CRS), Medical Certification of Causes of Death (MCCD), and Sample Registration System (SRS).
        </p>
