        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 border-b pb-2">
          Role of AIIMS Technical Support Unit (ATSU)
        </h3>
        <p>
          The AIIMS Technical Support Unit (ATSU) provides technical assistance to the Registrar General of India’s Office in conducting Verbal Autopsy-based Cause of Death Ascertainment under the Sample Registration System. This includes:
        </p>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2">
          <li>Identifying and liaising with institutions and individuals for physician coding of death based on verbal autopsy.</li>
          <li>Managing the web-based software for routing VA forms to physicians.</li>
          <li>Preparing and revising training manuals and conducting training sessions for various staff.</li>
          <li>Providing technical input on tools and processes used in the exercise.</li>
          <li>Undertaking quality control activities in both fieldwork and physician coding.</li>
          <li>Assisting in data analyses and report writing.</li>
          <li>Reviewing and verifying reports, publications, and dissemination materials.</li>
          <li>Holding meetings on technical issues as required.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

